@page
@model HealthcareSupport.CaseEvaluation.Pages.Account.ResendVerificationModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = Model.GetHeading();
}
@*
    Phase 1.D follow-up (Category 1, 2026-05-08) -- the resend-verification
    page rendered by ResendVerificationModel.

    Layout: inherits the AuthServer's _Layout via Pages/_ViewImports.cshtml +
    LeptonX theme; the wrapper div uses the same `account-card` /
    `account-content` class names ABP's stock Account/Login + Register pages
    use so visual rhythm (logo, card width, spacing, footer) stays
    consistent.

    Accessibility (Adrian Decision 2, 2026-05-08):
      - Single h1 declares the page topic per WCAG 2.1 SC 2.4.6.
      - The form has an explicit label for the email input + an
        aria-describedby pointing at the helper text below it.
      - The submit button gets a title attribute mirroring its visible
        label so AT users hear context even when scanning links.
      - Status / confirmation block uses role="status" + aria-live="polite"
        so screen readers announce changes to RequestSubmitted without
        moving focus.
      - Color contrast: relies on LeptonX defaults (passes WCAG AA).
      - Keyboard nav: the only interactive controls are the text input
        and submit button; default tab order works.

    Per Decision 3 (60-second cooldown), the form auto-disables the
    submit button for 60 seconds after a successful POST so the user
    cannot rapid-fire requests. Server-side rate-limit is the source of
    truth; the JS countdown is a UX hint, not security.
*@

<div class="account-card">
    <div class="account-content">

        <h1 class="text-center mt-4 mb-3">@Model.GetHeading()</h1>

        @if (Model.RequestSubmitted)
        {
            <div class="alert alert-success mt-3" role="status" aria-live="polite">
                <strong>Request received.</strong>
                <p class="mb-0">
                    If the address below matches an unverified account, a new
                    verification email is on its way. Check your inbox (and
                    spam folder) in the next few minutes. You can request
                    another email after 60 seconds if it does not arrive.
                </p>
            </div>
        }

        <p class="mt-3" id="resend-verification-intro">
            @Model.GetIntro()
        </p>

        <form method="post" asp-page="ResendVerification" novalidate>
            <input type="hidden" asp-for="Context" />

            <div class="form-group mt-3">
                <label asp-for="Email" class="form-label">Email address</label>
                <input asp-for="Email"
                       type="email"
                       class="form-control"
                       autocomplete="email"
                       inputmode="email"
                       aria-describedby="resend-verification-intro email-helper"
                       required />
                <span asp-validation-for="Email" class="text-danger"></span>
                <small id="email-helper" class="form-text text-muted">
                    Enter the email you used to register. We'll send a fresh
                    verification link to it.
                </small>
            </div>

            <div class="d-grid gap-2 mt-4">
                <button id="resend-verification-submit"
                        type="submit"
                        class="btn btn-primary btn-lg"
                        title="Send verification email">
                    Send verification email
                </button>
            </div>
        </form>

        <hr class="my-4" />

        <p class="text-center text-muted small">
            Already verified? <a href="~/Account/Login">Sign in</a>.
        </p>

    </div>
</div>

@section scripts {
    <script>
        // Phase 1.D follow-up: client-side cooldown UX hint. Server-side
        // rate-limit (60s in ExternalAccountAppService) is authoritative;
        // this just disables the button for a matching duration after a
        // successful POST so the user does not click again immediately.
        (function () {
            var submitted = @(Model.RequestSubmitted ? "true" : "false");
            if (!submitted) { return; }

            var btn = document.getElementById('resend-verification-submit');
            if (!btn) { return; }

            var cooldownSeconds = 60;
            var remaining = cooldownSeconds;
            var originalLabel = btn.innerText;

            btn.disabled = true;
            btn.setAttribute('aria-disabled', 'true');
            btn.innerText = 'Send verification email (' + remaining + 's)';

            var interval = setInterval(function () {
                remaining = remaining - 1;
                if (remaining <= 0) {
                    clearInterval(interval);
                    btn.disabled = false;
                    btn.removeAttribute('aria-disabled');
                    btn.innerText = originalLabel;
                    return;
                }
                btn.innerText = 'Send verification email (' + remaining + 's)';
            }, 1000);
        })();
    </script>
}
